dataIdInfo.idAbs: The dataset represents settlements of Ukraine (adm4 - Settlements). DISCLAIMER: Some errors are not addressed in this version. 61 Admin4 p-codes have inconsistent Admin2 p-code portions. Attribution nesting errors exist with the Admin2 layer. Admin3 and 4 p-codes both have 12 characters. 1,222 Admin4 p-codes are the same as their Admin3 p-codes.

dataLineage.statement:
Layer was downloaded by ITOS as a feature class within a file geodatabase from HDX. It was then analyzed by ITOS for errors. Those errors were corrected and then the layer was sent back to UNOCHA.
The following errors were found and fixed by ITOS: 1. Created and populated reference name field 2. As instructed by the IMO, ITOS has changed Admin4 Balta's 'admin2Name_en' to "Baltska", 'admin2Name_ua' to "Балтська", 'admin2Name_ru' to "Балтский" and 'admin2Pcode' to "UA51102".
Users should be aware that: - Admin4 is a places layer that does not cover the national extent.
- Admin4 does nest with Admin0, Admin1 and Admin3. Admin4 does NOT nest with Admin2. Specifically: • The Admin2 units "Kyivska", "Ivankivskyi" and "Lymanskyi" have inconsistent geometry nesting in the Admin4 layer • Admin2 units "Lymanskyi" (UA14230) and "Kyivska" (UA32100) are not represented in the Admin4 layer • Admin4 unit "Ilichanka" has attribution for Admin2 parent “Lymanskyi" but is spatially within the Admin2 unit “Odeska” • Admin4 unit "Prypiat" has attribution for Admin2 parent “Ivankivskyi" but is spatially within the Admin2 unit “Kyivska” • Admin4 units "Maiory" and "Povstanske" are attributed to fall within Admin2 unit “Biliaivska" but are spatially within the Admin2 unit “Biliaivskyi” • 36 Admin4 units have attribution for Admin2 “Lymanska" but are spatially within Admin2 “Lymanskyi”
- Admin3 and 4 p-codes both have 12 characters. 1,222 Admin4 p-codes are the same as their Admin3 p-codes. - 61 Admin4 p-codes have inconsistent Admin2 p-code portions - 28 Admin4 units exist with the same name within the same Admin3 parent. They have unique p-codes. - 707 English names in Admin4 do not have a 1 to 1 relationship with their alternate language names - 66 Admin4 units have holes that may represent lakes
